---
const faqs = [
  {
    q: 'How do I deploy chmonitor?',
    a: 'The fastest path is Docker: <code>docker run -d -p 3000:3000 -e CLICKHOUSE_HOST=... ghcr.io/duyet/chmonitor:latest</code>. It also deploys to <a href="https://docs.chmonitor.dev" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Cloudflare Workers</a> and Kubernetes via the bundled Helm chart. See the <a href="https://docs.chmonitor.dev" target="_blank" rel="noopener">quickstart</a> for step-by-step instructions.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Does it need exporters or agents installed on ClickHouse?',
    a: 'No. chmonitor reads ClickHouse system tables directly over the standard HTTP interface. There is no sidecar to run, no exporter to configure, and no extra storage to provision.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Is it safe to connect my production cluster?',
    a: 'Yes, when you use a read-only ClickHouse user. chmonitor only issues <code>SELECT</code> queries against system tables and never writes to your data. The AI agent is also read-only. You control what the connection user can access.',
  },
  {
    q: 'What is the performance impact on ClickHouse?',
    a: 'Low. All queries target system tables with a configurable execution timeout (default 60 s). Dashboard pages cache responses via TanStack Query so repeated views do not re-query the cluster.',
  },
  {
    q: 'What license is chmonitor under?',
    a: 'chmonitor is open source under the <a href="https://github.com/duyet/clickhouse-monitoring/blob/main/LICENSE" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GPL-3.0 license</a>. You are free to use, modify and redistribute it under those terms.',
  },
  {
    q: 'What is the difference between self-host and cloud?',
    a: 'Self-hosting gives you full control over deployment, data routing and configuration — and it is always free. The hosted cloud at <a href="https://dash.chmonitor.dev" target="_blank" rel="noopener">dash.chmonitor.dev</a> lets you connect a ClickHouse cluster without deploying anything. Cloud is currently in early access; pricing is not yet finalised.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Which ClickHouse versions are supported?',
    a: 'chmonitor uses version-aware SQL — queries adapt to the system table schema of the connected ClickHouse version. It is regularly tested against recent stable releases.',
  },
]

const faqJsonLd = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'FAQPage',
  mainEntity: faqs.map(({ q, a }) => ({
    '@type': 'Question',
    name: q,
    acceptedAnswer: {
      '@type': 'Answer',
      // strip HTML tags for the structured data text value
      text: a.replace(/<[^>]+>/g, ''),
    },
  })),
}
---
<script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(faqJsonLd)} />

<section id="faq" class="band band-soft">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="sec-head reveal">
      <span class="eyebrow">FAQ</span>
      <h2>Common questions</h2>
      <p>Answers to what evaluators ask most before deploying chmonitor.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-list reveal">
      {faqs.map(({ q, a }) => (
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>{q}</summary>
          <div class="faq-ans" set:html={a} />
        </details>
      ))}
    </div>

    <p style="margin-top:28px;font-size:14px;color:var(--muted-fg)" class="reveal">
      More questions? <a href="https://github.com/duyet/clickhouse-monitoring/discussions" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="color:var(--orange)">Ask on GitHub Discussions</a>.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
